🔒 2. Encapsulation

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is Encapsulation?

```text id="encapsulation_def"
Encapsulation is the process of restricting direct access to data and exposing it through methods.
```

---

🎯 Benefits

✔ Data security
✔ Controlled access
✔ Better maintainability

---

💻 Example

```python id="encapsulation_example"
class BankAccount:

    def __init__(self, balance):
        self.__balance = balance

    def get_balance(self):
        return self.__balance

account = BankAccount(5000)

print(
    account.get_balance()
)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="encapsulation_output"
5000
```

---

⚠️ Private Variables

Double underscore (`__`) makes variables private.

```python id="private_variable"
self.__balance
```

